Package berlin.hu.cep.connector

Class ZeebeSourceConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ConnectorConfig
      • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ZeebeConfig
        • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ZeebeSourceConfig
  • public class ZeebeSourceConfig
extends ZeebeConfig
    A class to configure a Zeebe Source Connector with sane defaults.

    The connector is designed to send simple events to a Siddhi instance for further processing.

    It also holds the attribute 'mongoDB_logging' which is not a configuration property of a Zeebe Source Connector. 'mongoDB_logging' is a way to enable logging in a MongoDB for the events which are sent from this source connector.

    An object of this class can be converted into a properties json file for the Zeebe Source Connector via the Jackson ObjectMapper.

    Author:
    Lukas Gehring, Leon Haussknecht, Maurice Lindner, Jost Hermann Triller, Stefan Zabka
    See Also:
    Kafka Connect connector for Zeebe

        Constructor for ZeebeSourceConfig. Note that since this class makes some assumptions not all configuration properties provided by the official Zeebe Source Connector can be set here.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the connector.
        mongoDB_logging - Enables logging of all related events into a MongDB database.
        job_types - a comma-separated list of job types that should be consumed by the connector
        job_header_topics - the custom service task header which specifies to which Kafka topics the message should be published to.
